@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>
    LoL Client Tool is a local learning project built with ASP.NET Core MVC.
    The application runs on your own computer and is designed to interact with your locally running League of Legends Client.
</p>

<h2>What This App Uses</h2>

<p>
    This app checks whether the League Client is running and reads the local League Client lockfile.
    The lockfile is used to find the local port, protocol, and password needed to communicate with the League Client API on your computer.
</p>

<p>
    This information is only used while the app is running so that it can send local requests to the League Client, such as changing your profile icon.
</p>

<h2>What This App Does Not Collect</h2>

<p>
    This app does not collect, store, upload, sell, or share your personal information.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>It does not store your League account details.</li>
    <li>It does not store your League Client lockfile data.</li>
    <li>It does not store or display the League Client password from the lockfile.</li>
    <li>It does not send your League Client password to any external server.</li>
    <li>It does not track your usage.</li>
    <li>It does not use analytics or advertising cookies.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Local League Client API</h2>

<p>
    The app communicates with the League Client API running locally on your computer.
    This connection is used only for the features available inside this tool.
</p>

<h2>Unofficial Project</h2>

<p>
    LoL Client Tool is an unofficial fan-made learning project.
    It is not endorsed by Riot Games and does not represent Riot Games or League of Legends.
</p>